cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with text classification and introduces a new approach to self-attention modules for capturing features from different scales. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new model for text classification and compares its performance with the standard Transformer model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to self-attention modules that can be applied to various natural language processing tasks. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses multi-scale self-attention, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision tasks. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a new neural network architecture for text classification.
